The attached information comes from
papers filed with  Japan 's Ministry of Finance related to changes
in significant shareholders. The papers were filed on March 23.
* Refers to Group Total.  Only shareholders who own or owned more than 5 percent and
had a change holdings are included. Percentage owned takes into
account all issued and outstanding shares, as well as all
potential shares. That includes equity warrants, convertible
bonds, covered warrants, depositary receipts and callable
convertible bonds. Preferred shares that may be converted into
common shares are also taken into account. Filings for 
correction are excluded.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven McPherson in Tokyo at 
 smcpherson@bloomberg.net   To contact the reporters for this story:
Kazuyo Sawa in Tokyo at 
